<xml xmlns="https://developers.google.com/blockly/xml"><comment id="(bL.dDC2Ll(8kE5?kS/n" x="-37" y="-93" h="708" w="536">Decide what you're going to have as random choices! &#10;&#10;1) Make a variable.&#10;&#10;2) Drag a red "set variable to" block into the input.&#10;&#10;3) In the math section, find the block that says "pick random" and replace the 0 in the set variable block. Choose the number of choices you want to have! Must be at least 2.&#10;&#10;4) Grab an "if true then else" conditional block and put it inside the input as well.  &#10;&#10;5) Drag the 0=0 block that's in the workspace to replace the "true" in the conditional block.&#10;&#10;6) Put a red, circular variable block to replace the first 0 after "if." Then, change the second 0 to be one of the numbers you chose to be randomly selected. &#10;&#10;7) Underneath the "if variable = number, then" space, put in what you want to display. It could be words, symbols, or numbers.&#10;&#10;8) Do the same for under the "else" section.&#10;&#10;9) If you have more than 2 choices, click the plus sign under "else" to add more! You'll need to duplicate the "variable = number" block and put it in, then change the number.&#10;&#10;Share, add your name to the file, copy the link and submit!</comment><block type="device_button_event" id="`,9u~FNd{DEA5SCZ{-])" x="529" y="-73"><field name="NAME">Button.A</field></block><block type="logic_compare" id="zow_Xqm(z?_o#Y%}:LZr" disabled="true" x="552" y="168"><field name="OP">EQ</field><value name="A"><shadow type="math_number" id="QaA/~kkX`G`tf`@EJ(/x"><field name="NUM">0</field></shadow></value><value name="B"><shadow type="math_number" id=",#1lkH9G=9.}c1{z].V]"><field name="NUM">0</field></shadow></value></block></xml>